features: ⚡【100W USB C Fast Charging】JSAUX 100W usb c charger cable has PD and QC fast charging technology, supports up to 100W (20V/5A) output with usb-c power delivery adapters such as 30W/45W/60W/65W/96W/100W. Charge MacBook Pro 16” up to 68% in 35mins, charge Samsung Galaxy S24/S23 up to 92% in 35mins. (NOTE: The actual charging speed depends on your device and wall charger.)

✅【Charge Your iPhone 15 at Full Speed】With JSAUX lightning-speed 100W USB-C to USB-C cable, your iPhone 15 series reaches a whopping 71% battery in just 30 minutes. With its high power output, it can deliver a quick charge to your device, allowing you to get back to using your iPhone in no time.

💗【Sleek and Transparent Design】JSAUX brand new USB-C charging cable not only features advanced charging technology but also boasts a unique and stylish design with a transparent casing while adding a touch of fashion to your charging experience. With this cable, you can enjoy both cutting-edge charging capabilities and a one-of-a-kind fashion statement.

💡【The Safest Fast E-Marker Smart Chip】This usbc to usbc cable has a built-in SUPER E-MARK chip, which will intelligently identify the charging device and its charging power, thus adjusting the appropriate voltage and current to provide the fastest fast charging power without overloading and protecting your device's battery.

💪【Durable and Long-Lasting】Upgraded 3D aluminum connector and exclusive laser welding technology, which ensure the metal part won't break easily. Premium nylon braided cable adds additional durability and makes it tangle free. Special Strain Relief design, can bear 20,000+ bending test.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exceptional Charging Performance and Versatility
reviews.reviewText: The JSAUX 100W USB C to USB C Cable has proven to be a game-changer in the world of charging accessories. This two-pack of 6.6FT cables demonstrates an unparalleled blend of quality, durability, and compatibility, making it a standout choice for users across various devices.The standout feature of these cables is their impressive 100W capacity, ensuring lightning-fast charging for a multitude of devices, including the latest iPhone 15 Pro Max, iPad, MacBook, Galaxy, and Pixel. The speed and efficiency with which these cables transfer power is truly remarkable, providing a swift and reliable charging experience.The build quality of the cables is top-notch, with a sturdy construction that feels both robust and flexible. The reinforced connectors and durable cable sheath inspire confidence in longevity, ensuring these cables withstand the rigors of daily use without sacrificing performance.The white color not only adds a touch of elegance but also makes it easy to locate the cables in any setting. The length of 6.6FT strikes a perfect balance, offering ample reach without unnecessary tangling or clutter.One of the key advantages of these cables is their broad compatibility. Whether you're charging your iPhone, iPad, MacBook, Galaxy device, or Pixel, these cables seamlessly adapt to each device's unique charging requirements, eliminating the need for multiple cables for different gadgets.In conclusion, the JSAUX 100W USB C to USB C Cable is a stellar performer in every aspect. Its exceptional charging speed, robust build, and universal compatibility make it an indispensable accessory for tech enthusiasts. Investing in this cable ensures a hassle-free and efficient charging experience, earning it a well-deserved 5 out of 5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality USB-C cables from JSAUX
reviews.reviewText: I have long been a big fan of cables from JSAUX. They’re always well-made and I haven’t yet had to replace any of them (USB, HDMI, DisplayPort). These cables feel just as high quality as the other JSAUX cables. The cable itself is braided and each comes with an attached hook-and-loop cable so you can wrap up any excess cord. The ends have a clear see-through plastic casing and the power rating (100 watts) is printed on one end of the cable. I don’t have anything that consumes 100 watts but I do have a battery pack that can be charged at a rate of 65 watts. These cables charged the battery pack at 65 watts (though the reading read slightly higher than 65 watts) and the connectors never got hot. The only negative I can think of is that these cables are white and will probably look dirty at some point but that’s just a nitpick. Overall these are great high quality USB-C cables!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Two quality cables from JSAUX
reviews.reviewText: This set consists of two cables, each about two meters long, with a thick braided white cable body and a distinctive white/acrylic/metallic plug on each end. The ends are formed from a metal core covered by acrylic, keeping them relatively scratch free, and the ends and included velcro cable ties are silk screened with "100W" to help document what the current carrying capacity of this cable is, which is appreciated.I tested charging multiple laptops, including my MacBook Air 15", with these and it worked like a charm at full charging speed. They seem in spec and to have a proper eMarker as required by USB-C standards.JSAUX has quickly developed a name for themselves as a reliable accessory brand, starting with Steam Deck accessories and branching out from there. I'm pleased to discover their cables are just as nice as their other accessories, and I'll keep an eye out for more of these in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice White Cable
reviews.reviewText: This is a good looking cable even though it is plain white. The cable feels durable and works as expected. This looks like those cheap vinyl usb cables,, but it is actually nylon braided. There is no transparent shell, so I don’t know what that means. The data transfer rate is slow, which means this will mainly be used for charging.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These come packaged in a little box, that makes them giftable if you'd like. Each of the transparent portions are wrapped in a plastic liner to make sure they don't get any scratches on them before they arrive, as well as some plastic casings for the C-ports. As a bonus, it comes with two cord wraps to keep them inline.The cable itself is really great. It's nice and flexible, and can bend into a tight enough circle to fit my thumb through. The braiding is very pleasant and soft to the touch, as actual fabric instead of nylon thread, though even a day out of the package I found that it has some abrasion fluff/tearing near the heads of the cord. I love the touch of the transparent plastic, but it does make the head of the cord longer than most.Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality build and nice length
reviews.reviewText: The look and feel of these cables appear that they are quality built. The length is perfect for using my laptop or phone without having to be tied down near an outlet. They work good on all of my devices and stay cool during heavy charging times even when connected to a high wattage charging block. The velcro strap on the cables make storing them neater and keeps them from coming uncoiled. The first impression of quality was that each connector being capped when I opened the package, The caps are very useful during storing the cables either in a drawer or in my backpack to protect the connectors from being damaged. The connectors are nicely put together and appear to be very solid in construction. I anticipate that these cables will last for a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: They're nice and long so you can keep them plugged in while scrolling in bed, which the internet assures us we shouldn't be doing, but you know we're going to. They're wrapped in a sturdy nylon-ish rope to keep the from breaking or wearing out and seem very durable. The nicest charge cords I've used.
